Are you age 16+ and a member of an unserved community?
A multigenerational household includes with 3 or more generations, or “skipped” generations (e.g., a grandchild living with an elder)

A served community is one in which more than 55% of homes are served by a piped, septic tank & well, or covered haul system. An unserved community is one where 45% or more homes have not been served either via pipe, septic tank & well, or covered haul system.
